news.title: About 100% hike in collectorate guideline rates proposed in five locations near Bhopal metro
news.para: According to assessment, expected completion of Bhopal metro is in 2026. It includes two lines, one under-construction Karond to AIIMS Bhopal. Another is Bhadbhada to Ratnagiri.

news.title: Gujarat assembly passes amendment bill on transfer fees collected by housing societies
news.para: ​​​​​Through an amendment, the BJP government inserted a new section in the Gujarat Co-operative Societies Act, 1961, which says "a co-operative housing society or a cooperative housing service society shall not collect transfer fee more than the transfer fee as may be prescribed".

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to carry out 'voluntary' Aadhaar seeding of property records
news.para: The Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) is expecting a total receipts of Rs 12,371.63 crore comprising its opening balance of Rs 8,294.04 crore and central and state grants of Rs 4,077.59 crore.

news.title: Delhi LG objects to delay in finalisation of lease deeds for flats under RGHS
news.para: The Rajiv Gandhi Housing Scheme -- RGHS-I and RGHS-II -- were initiated in 2003-04 and 2006-07, but the draft lease deed to be executed for allotment of flats reached the Lt Governor for his approval in January 2024, officials said.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to restrain creation of additional tenements for PAPs
news.para: The court heard three PILs by BJP leader Kirit Somaiya and two others. Somaiya alleged a scam in BMC’s scheme for the “benefit of certain developers”.

news.title: Gurugram: Now, software to help town planner pick OCs for checks
news.para: Till now, 10% of OCs granted to properties by architects under the self-certification scheme were checked at random by the planning wing of DTCP, but the selection was done manually.

news.title: Delhi civic body extends last date or geo-tagging properties till March 31
news.para: Earlier, the last date was January 31, which was extended once to February 29.

news.title: Kesoram completes Rs 1,900 crore high-cost debt refinancing
news.para: On Thursday, the company announced the redemption of the entire outstanding outstanding NCD amounting to Rs 1487 crore before maturity. OCDs were redeemed earlier, officials said.

news.title: Mumbai: Enforcement directorate seizes Rs 7 crore properties of Ornate Spaces
news.para: Last month, ED arrested Machinder who is in jail custody. He had planned to construct Grove Tower on a plot available for open market sale, aimed at developing residences for UTI staff.

news.title: Cabinet approves Rs 75,000 crore rooftop solar scheme
news.para: "The Union Cabinet, chaired by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, has approved PM-Surya Ghar: Muft Bijli Yojana with a total outlay of Rs 75,021 crore for installing rooftop solar and providing free electricity up to 300 units every month for one crore households," an official statement said.

news.title: Property registrations in Mumbai up 24% in February
news.para: In February last year, 9,684 units were registered, real estate consultant Knight Frank India said, which sourced the data from the Maharashtra government.

news.title: With investment of Rs 50,000 crore, Uttar Pradesh's realty sector set for a boom: Government
news.para: "Many prominent real estate firms, including from within India and abroad, have initiated their projects in Uttar Pradesh. It includes M3M India Private Limited, which is investing Rs 7,500 crore to develop residential, commercial, official, retail, and service apartments.

news.title: ED attaches flats-plots worth Rs 64 crore of Kamla Landmarc
news.para: In a press release issued on Thursday, the ED stated that Jitendra Jain, in a criminal conspiracy with Parvath Shetty, transferred ownership of Kamla Landmarc Builders

news.title: Transindia Real Estate to sell its logistics park in Jhajjar for Rs 636.71 crore
news.para: Transindia Real Estate has divested its 10% stake held in Malur Logistics & Industrial Parks, Venkatapura Logistics & Industrial Parks, Kalina Warehousing, Panvel Warehousing, and Allcargo Logistics & Industrial Park, for an equity consideration of near Rs 4.55 crore.

news.title: Britain's Taylor Wimpley to build fewer houses in 2024 amidst limited supply
news.para: The British housebuilder said its first-half operating profit margin would reflect slightly lower pricing in the homes it has coming through, citing cost inflation and investment.

news.title: Hong Kong agents say property deals jump after big policy moves
news.para: Hong Kong, long among the world's most expensive housing markets, saw prices plunge 20% from their 2021 peak, hurt by the pandemic, an exodus of residents triggered by Beijing's imposition of the national security law and interest rate hikes.

news.title: Making construction sites safer with AI technology
news.para: In general, through diverse AI forms, including machine learning and deep learning, construction companies can accurately identify risks faster, monitor real-time progress, detect potential hazards and make informed decisions to address issues in the construction process.

news.title: Holcim posts profit of 1.12 billion Swiss francs in Q4 2023
news.para: The Swiss cement maker, which last month announced plans to spin off its fast-growing American business, was in confident mood after posting record annual operating profit on the back of efficiency gains and price increases.

news.title: Home building permits in Germany dips 27% in 2023
news.para: Some 260,100 permits were issued, which is 94,100 fewer permits than in 2022 and the lowest since 2012, The number of building permits is an important indicator of future construction.
